{"lemma":"حَسَنَةٌ","slug":"حَسَنَةٌ","root":"ح.س.ن","root_slug":"ح-س-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-س-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَسَنَة","root":"حسن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":31},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8012"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good deed, benefaction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charity, alms"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"advantage, merit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"well-being, good times"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of حَسَن (ḥasan)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare حَسُنَ (ḥasuna, “to be good”). Cognate with Hebrew חֹסֶן (khōsen, “wealth, treasure”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8012","headword_ar":"حَسَنَةٌ","root":"Hsn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  Also, [used as a subst., or as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A good act"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"often particularly applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an alms-deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ksh and Bd in iv. 80:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a good action"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Er-Rághib, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good, benefit, benefaction, boon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh and Bd ibid.:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~iy^apN","text_ar":"سَيِّيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in all these senses]: (S, K:) as contr. of this latter word, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any rejoicing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladdening, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that betides a man in his soul and his body and his circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanaAtN","text_ar":"حَسَنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, and Kur vii. 167, &c.:) it has no broken pl. (TA.) Hence, in the Kur iv. 80, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abundance of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the goods, conveniences, and comforts, of life; ampleness of circumstances; and success:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~iy^ap","text_ar":"سَيِّيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"there means the contr. of these. (Er-Rághib, TA.) In the Kur xi. 116,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasanaAt","text_ar":"الحَسَنَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The five daily prayers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expiating what has been between them. (TA.) ―         -b3-  As an epithet, [fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] it is applied to an accident as well as to a substance. (Er-Rághib, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}